{
  "stem": "18581.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 289.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was only one synagogue in our town, as this was a new town, comparatively.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when the reader, the Torah reader was away, or was not well, then my father used to read the Torah.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I mean that the country, to most towns in Lithuania, 150 years ago, our town was just a village on a farm by a person called Mazeika And when the Russian government, the czar, brought the [NON-ENGLISH] railroad line to [NON-ENGLISH] via Mazeikiai, then the railroad brought a great deal of life, especially since they also built a road-- a railroad from Mazeikiai to Riga.",
      "word_count": 65
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then, of course, being the center of a railroad, of-- of course the station, and the-- the-- the people that-- that worked around the railroad, during the Russian times, there was also a railroad school and also a huge workshops to build and repair locomotives and railroad cars.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The last czar.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That would be, I guess-- what was his name?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The last Romanoff, anyway.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The last Romanoff.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So, the Russian government.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father very much wanted to-- to do so, and actually encouraged my late sister, Gita, to go on [NON-ENGLISH] and prepare herself in Lithuania on a farm, and then go to Palestine, which she did in 19-- I believe-- 34.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my father very much wanted to-- to do so.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it was not so easy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was a economic crisis in Lithuania, as it was in most of Europe in the '30s.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the money was very tight.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You sell-- you sold many-- mostly on credit.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Otherwise, people couldn't afford to buy-- in installments.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was very difficult to collect quickly and to capitalize and-- [INAUDIBLE] and go away.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
